do set-up jenkins dashboard like below

sudo yum update â€“y
sudo wget -O /etc/yum.repos.d/jenkins.repo https://pkg.jenkins.io/redhat-stable/jenkins.repo
sudo rpm --import https://pkg.jenkins.io/redhat-stable/jenkins.io-2023.key
sudo yum upgrade
sudo yum install java-17-amazon-corretto -y
sudo yum install jenkins git -y
sudo systemctl enable jenkins
sudo systemctl start jenkins
sudo systemctl status jenkins

above all commands to set-up a Jenkins Dashboard

what is pipeline
===================

It is a group of stages that are interlinked with each other to perform an action

we are using to deploy the application

2 types of pipelines
1. free-style pipeline
2. pipeline

create a new job----------> select pipeline option ----------> in here we will write pipeline

pipeline {
    agent any
    stages {
        stage ("Code") {
            steps {
                echo "welcome to february 2026"
            }
        }
    }
}

save --------> build

Build got success & Output as --------> welcome to february 2026


Always remember there is only one step inside a stage

pipeline {
    agent any
    stages {
        stage ("Code") {
            steps {
                echo "welcome to february 2026"
            }
        }
        stage ("Build") {
            steps {
                echo "Happy Tailor's Day"
            }
        }
        stage ("Test") {
            steps {
                echo "This is testing stage"
            }
        }
    }
}

save --------> build

Build got success

if we want to see the output we can see in console output

go to manage jenkins-------> selet available plugins------> search as pipeline stage-view-----> install it

pipeline stage-view plugin is used to view the job Builds output as stage view

pipeline {
    agent any
    stages {
        stage ("Code") {
            steps {
                sh 'touch files'
                sh 'mkdir folders'
                sh 'cal'
            }
        }
        stage ("Stage-2") {
            steps {
                echo "this is my stage-2"
                sh 'timedatectl'
            }
        }
    }
}

save --------> build

Build got success

pipeline {
    agent any
    stages {
        stage ("Commands") {
            steps {
                sh '''
                   touch files name
                   mkdir folder name
                   cal
                   timedatectl
                   '''
            }
        }
    }
}

above pipeline to give all commands at a time



save --------> build

Build got success


pipeline {
    agent any
    stages {
        stage ("Code") {
            steps {
                git branch: 'main', url: 'https://github.com/pranay-devops666/Python-Automation-Scripts.git'
            }
        }
    }
}

save --------> build

Build got success



pipeline {
    agent any
    tools {
        maven 'mymaven'
    }
    stages {
        stage ("Code") {
            steps {
                git branch: 'main', url: 'https://github.com/pranay-devops666/Python-Automation-Scripts.git'
            }
        }
        stage ("Build") {
            steps {
                sh 'mvn clean package'
            }
        }
    }
}
save --------> build

Build got success
